te cell reproduction and hypertrophy\nSecondly, TSH stimulates the thyroid gland t0 synthesize and secrete T3 and T4.\nability t0 quantitate circulating levels of TSH is important in evaluating thyroid function. It is especially useful in the differential diagnosis of primary (thyroid) fromi\nsecondary (pituitary) and tertiary (hypothalamus) hypothyroidism. In primary hypothyroidism, TSH levels are significantly elevated, while in secondary and tertiary\nhypothyroidism, TSH levels are low_\n*xx\nEnd Of Report\n*xx\nDr Pratap Patil\nDr. Saumya Gupta\nDr Balraj Raj\nMD (Patholoav)\nMD DNB\nPathologist\nAlumnus PGIMER;\n(M.DMBBS)\nChandigarh\nPowered by:\nBIOGENE LABS\nCENTRALISED LAB:\nstay\nThe\npRai",
